        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:31PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 231 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with frequent
lightning along a line extending from 7 miles northeast of Pickens to
11 miles north of Hartwell, and moving southeast at 20 mph.

Locations to be impacted include...
Easley, Clemson, Pickens, Anderson, Powdersville, Central, Northlake,
Pendleton, Liberty, and Norris.

In addition to intense lightning, very heavy rainfall rates up to 2
inches per hour and gusty wind will be possible in these areas.
</description>
